text:
Blacklist story Blacklist domain After​ last September's big blowup at Cape Canaveral, progress with SpaceX's launches appears to be progressing nicely after this morning's successful launch and first stage recovery . Throughout the day different clips have made their way online — here are the best: Here's the New York Times with the launch: THE NEW YORK TIMES The stage separation starts here at around 22:22: SpaceX The recovery at a long distance: SpaceX A post shared by Elon Musk (@elonmusk) on Feb 19, 2017 at 12:20pm PST 
Digg is what the internet is talking about, right now. It's also the website you are currently on. FOR THE LONG WEEKEND
